# The Dark One · the imprisoned source of the Shadow

The Dark One — Shai'tan — is the imprisoned antithesis of the Creator. He is not a being within the Pattern but the very force of entropy, chaos, and unmaking, pressing against the weave of existence from outside time itself. Where the Creator is making, he is its undoing; he stands opposed to all that is woven and turned.

Sealed away at the moment of creation, his prison has been breached and resealed across the Ages. The bonds that hold him are not eternal in their security but a recurring struggle, broken and mended as the Wheel turns. His touch taints and corrupts, and even the strongest may be turned to the Shadow under its weight.

He matters to the turning of the Wheel as the ultimate threat to the Pattern itself: not a foe to be merely defeated, but a pressure that would unmake all weaving if his prison failed. To speak his true name is to draw his eye, and so even the naming of him carries danger.

His nature of emergence is ethereal because he is no embodied figure of the world but the Shadow's outside-time evil — a force beyond the channeled Power and beyond the flesh, belonging to that order of things that touch the Pattern from without rather than living within it.
